1
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:35,800
Isn't this a random move?

2
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:36,880
No.

3
00:01:36,880 --> 00:01:39,360
How can you call this a random move?

4
00:01:41,039 --> 00:01:42,280
I think

5
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:45,920
the master is doing this to mess with the opponent's mind.

6
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:47,780
You've already messed with mine.

7
00:01:49,240 --> 00:01:49,720
I...

8
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:51,479
Mr. Qin, Mr. Zhao.

9
00:01:53,759 --> 00:01:55,280
I'm sorry, I...

10
00:01:55,479 --> 00:01:56,560
Sorry for what?

11
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,400
Don't you already know

12
00:01:58,400 --> 00:02:01,080
that the simulated flight control failed? So...

13
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:01,600
So what?

14
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:04,720
Running back to the archives after a loss,

15
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:06,120
is this where you belong?

16
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:07,960
Wu Wei,

17
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:09,410
what do you mean?

18
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:12,240
What do you think my archives are?

19
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:12,880
A backup?

20
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:14,640
You couldn't get into flight control,

21
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:16,560
so you come here looking dejected.

22
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:17,480
If you're going to be like this,

23
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:19,079
you better leave now.

24
00:02:19,320 --> 00:02:20,000
I won't keep you here.

25
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:20,680
No.

26
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:21,760
No, Mr. Zhao, you misunderstood.

27
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:22,920
That's not what I meant.

28
00:02:22,920 --> 00:02:24,240
I will adjust my attitude right away

29
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:25,040
and work hard.

30
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:27,760
When we were young,

31
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:30,640
we didn't have time for this nonsense.

32
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:32,680
We spent all our time on work.

33
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:37,079
Why are you still standing here?

34
00:02:37,079 --> 00:02:38,000
Hurry up and go.

35
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:40,410
Mr. Zhao, please don't kick me out.

36
00:02:40,640 --> 00:02:43,370
There are ten minutes until the morning meeting.

37
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:48,260
You'll be late if you don't go now.

38
00:02:50,480 --> 00:02:52,240
Do you mean I can go back to flight control?

39
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,400
Wu Wei.

40
00:02:53,760 --> 00:02:55,160
I think you're usually

41
00:02:55,160 --> 00:02:56,800
quite thick-skinned.

42
00:02:57,400 --> 00:03:00,600
Why do you become a yo-yo when it comes to serious matters?

43
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:02,480
No, no.

44
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:03,340
Come back here.

45
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,560
I can tell you now.

46
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:31,520
Mr. Qian gave me this pen.

47
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:33,850
I've cherished it all these years.

48
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:34,800
I'm giving it to you.

49
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,280
Consider yourself lucky, kid.

50
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:36,960
Mr...

51
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:38,520
Mr. Qian.

52
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:39,120
Yes.

53
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:40,800
It's too precious. No, no, no.

54
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:41,880
Stop dawdling.

55
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:43,360
Take it and work hard.

56
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:45,520
Just don't embarrass the Archives.

57
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:49,040
Hurry up and go, or I'll regret it.

58
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:49,600
Yes.

59
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:50,720
Hurry up.

60
00:03:51,520 --> 00:03:52,000
And,

61
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:52,880
Wu Wei.

62
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:03,040
China Aerospace.

63
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:04,440
I hope you can

64
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:06,160
live up to this title.

65
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:23,040
Sorry for making you spend a fortune.

66
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:25,920
It really hurts.

67
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:27,320
I did spend a fortune.

68
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:29,930
But I listened to what you said.

69
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:32,880
Nothing ventured, nothing gained.

70
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:39,840
What is this?

71
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:44,920
I know you couldn't bear to part with it.

72
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:46,400
So I bought another one,

73
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:47,440
an identical pen.

74
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:49,040
When you weren't looking,

75
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,400
I swapped it.

76
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:54,159
This is the one Mr. Qian gave you.

77
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:57,760
Returned intact to its rightful owner.

78
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:05,060
You're really something.

79
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:06,960
You old fox.

80
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:09,800
Alright. Good for you.

81
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:00,880
The reason Muxing Team failed the flight simulation this time

82
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:02,760
is that I ignored the actual situation

83
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:04,820
and insisted on using a radical plan.

84
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:06,080
Please supervise me.

85
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:07,960
I will try my best to catch up with everyone

86
00:06:07,960 --> 00:06:10,090
and become a qualified Muxing member.

87
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:14,240
Mr. Chu.

88
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,720
I know I

89
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:17,400
lack ability but have a bad temper.

90
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:18,800
Please be magnanimous

91
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,690
and give me another chance.

92
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:24,320
Being late in a space mission

93
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:25,720
could cause an accident.

94
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,000
Sit down quickly.

95
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:27,800
Yes.

96
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:30,640
All right, let's start the meeting.

97
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:32,040
I believe you've heard

98
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:32,640
that the center

99
00:06:32,640 --> 00:06:34,920
has been preparing for the Xingqiao relay satellite mission

100
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:36,600
to provide communication support for Haoyue 4's

101
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,280
landing on the far side of the moon.

102
00:06:38,280 --> 00:06:39,520
This is also the world's first

103
00:06:39,520 --> 00:06:41,040
telemetry, tracking, command, and relay communication

104
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:42,960
at the Earth-Moon Lagrange L2 point.

105
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:44,360
Currently, we have selected

106
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:45,960
the halo orbit at the Earth-Moon L2 point

107
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:47,120
as the Xingqiao orbit.

108
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:48,040
So what we need to do

109
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:50,200
is to help Xingqiao find a path

110
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:52,330
that smoothly leads to the halo orbit.

111
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:54,720
Later, the four of you will

112
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:56,040
participate in some of the work,

113
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:58,040
starting with orbit data calculation.

114
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:59,000
You can go to the institute in a while

115
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,330
and bring the data back.

116
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:02,200
Since the simulated flight is over,

117
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:02,760
from now on,

118
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:04,440
I will hold you to higher standards.

119
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:05,880
I hope you can pull yourselves together

120
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:07,210
and meet the challenge.

121
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:15,730
The detector workshop.

122
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:17,040
Take a look.

123
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:21,560
This is the most important department in satellite manufacturing.

124
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:22,720
From assembly to integration,

125
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:24,960
and the many tests required for R&D,

126
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:26,800
the satellites you see operating in orbit

127
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:27,920
are all born here.

128
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:29,240
Look at this.

129
00:07:29,440 --> 00:07:32,040
This is our Haoyue 4 Xingqiao relay satellite.

130
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:33,360
What do you think?

131
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:35,240
Don't blink.

132
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:38,159
This is our Earth-Moon communication

133
00:07:38,159 --> 00:07:39,800
and data relay station.

134
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:42,000
It can transmit the scientific data

135
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,640
of Haoyue-4, which landed on the lunar far side,

136
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:45,100
back to Earth in real time.

137
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:46,960
It's equivalent to

138
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:50,760
a fiber-optic network relay station between the Earth and the moon.

139
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:55,260
Precisely because it is blocked by the moon itself,

140
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:59,730
we must build Xingqiao on the Earth-Moon extension line

141
00:07:59,960 --> 00:08:03,840
to achieve communication visibility with the lunar far side and Earth.

142
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:04,720
Ultimately,

143
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:06,560
this is a powerful attempt by humanity

144
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:07,960
to explore deep space.

145
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:09,960
It has great scientific

146
00:08:09,960 --> 00:08:11,360
and engineering significance.

147
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:12,200
My God.

148
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:14,800
This is simply industrial aesthetics.

149
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,060
With this star bridge,

150
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:17,440
our journey to the far side of the moon

151
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:18,880
will be a smooth ride.

152
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,490
This is so spectacular.

153
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:23,400
I should have studied the next major over,

154
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:26,000
so I wouldn't have to wrestle with data all day.

155
00:08:26,960 --> 00:08:28,000
For such a huge project,

156
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,640
we definitely have to cooperate.

157
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:30,240
Right?

158
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:33,480
This is the result of the joint efforts of hundreds of sister units,

159
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:34,520
tens of thousands of scientists,

160
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:36,360
and engineers.

161
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:40,159
It relies on collective wisdom, strength, and struggle.

162
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:41,520
Of course,

163
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:43,640
your Brother Xiu also gets some credit for this.

164
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:44,770
Testing over there.

165
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:49,920
I hope I can stay

166
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:52,580
to help the probe land on the moon.

167
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:53,400
Mr. You,

168
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:55,480
the orbit data you need to calculate is over here.

169
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:56,080
Follow me.

170
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:56,560
All right.

171
00:08:56,560 --> 00:08:57,090
This way.

172
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:02,600
This.

173
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:04,080
This.

174
00:09:05,040 --> 00:09:06,840
Don't just stand there. Take it.

175
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,360
The orbit data to be calculated later

176
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:09,040
is all here.

177
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:10,640
Catch.

178
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:14,000
This is...

179
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:14,960
This is...

180
00:09:22,760 --> 00:09:23,760
Let me help you.

181
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:25,320
Thank you.

182
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:26,120
Who put

183
00:09:27,280 --> 00:09:28,400
this here?

184
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:33,930
Did you receive the cup Wu Wei gave you?

185
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:40,040
You can use that cup

186
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:41,360
to make hot tea or something.

187
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:43,490
Don't always use paper cups for water.

188
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:47,040
Jiajia,

189
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:48,880
the registration for this year's Space Orbit Competition

190
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:49,920
has started.

191
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:51,600
You guys in Flight Control should participate.

192
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:52,800
Hello, Director Cao.

193
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:55,280
I think it will be tough this year.

194
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:57,280
With such heavy tasks, how would they have time?

195
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:58,610
Didn't Mr. Qin tell you?

196
00:09:58,880 --> 00:10:01,360
He told me to come to you.

197
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:02,240
It's up to you.

198
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:05,200
I know you have heavy tasks,

199
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:08,320
but haven't a few newcomers arrived this year?

200
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:10,600
Let the kids participate

201
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,040
and practice.

202
00:10:12,520 --> 00:10:13,800
The simulation flight failed.

203
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:15,160
Are you still counting on them?

204
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:16,680
Is it that bad?

205
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:20,080
They're already quite upset about the simulation flight failure.

206
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:21,760
I heard the competition is harder this year,

207
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:23,120
and the opponents are stronger.

208
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:24,080
I'm worried that if I go,

209
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:25,880
I might not do well in the competition.

210
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:28,010
Never mind. Let's talk about it later.

211
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:29,600
What should we do then?

212
00:10:30,280 --> 00:10:32,520
How about you ask other departments?

213
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:36,520
Aren't you making things difficult for me?

214
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:37,440
Director Cao.

215
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:51,000
I haven't recovered from the flight simulation,

216
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:53,560
and now I have to calculate new orbital data.

217
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:55,960
So stressful.

218
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:57,760
I'm traumatized.

219
00:10:58,240 --> 00:10:59,640
I'm afraid of making mistakes in whatever I do.

220
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:02,480
This is a place where results speak for themselves.

221
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:03,640
We messed up before.

222
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:05,920
Don't blame them for looking down on us.

223
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:08,040
If we want them to respect us,

224
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:10,770
we have to conquer them.

225
00:11:12,520 --> 00:11:13,780
How do we conquer them?

226
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:19,040
Today I heard a Director Cao

227
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:22,120
talking to Jia about this.

228
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:24,960
I think it's our chance.

229
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:32,880
I know this competition.

230
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:33,840
It's an international event

231
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:34,960
held every two years.

232
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:37,080
In recent years, it's been dominated by the World Aerospace Association

233
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:39,280
and the Western Space Development Alliance.

234
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:40,940
The opponents are too strong.

235
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:41,520
Yes.

236
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:42,980
If we fight,

237
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:45,090
we should fight the strongest.

238
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:47,480
Second place was the Chinese team's

239
00:11:47,480 --> 00:11:48,600
best result before.

240
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:50,000
Today, Director Cao

241
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:51,120
wanted to ask Sister Jia

242
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:53,880
to let our department participate in this competition,

243
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:54,920
but was rejected.

244
00:11:55,160 --> 00:11:55,920
I think

245
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:57,560
we can sign up ourselves.

246
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:58,360
Right?

247
00:11:58,560 --> 00:11:59,560
This competition

248
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:02,200
is the most professional one in deep space exploration

249
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:03,320
and orbit design.

250
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:05,080
If we get any ranking,

251
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:06,730
we will take off.

252
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:08,240
But Sister Jia refused.

253
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:09,570
How can we participate?

254
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:12,520
Just don't let her know.

255
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,640
We can finish it in our spare time.

256
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:16,520
Then we can redeem ourselves.

257
00:12:16,760 --> 00:12:17,920
Isn't it a win-win?

258
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:23,120
I guess it's doable.

259
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:24,600
If we don't get good grades,

260
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,040
it's the participation that counts.

261
00:12:26,040 --> 00:12:27,480
If we give it a try

262
00:12:27,560 --> 00:12:28,760
and get a good result,

263
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:30,960
we'll hit the jackpot.

264
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:33,920
If you are all okay with it,

265
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:35,380
then I have no objections.

266
00:12:36,640 --> 00:12:37,960
Ying Ziqi, join us.

267
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:39,200
Of course.

268
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:42,160
I'm counting on Master Ying to dominate the field.

269
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:49,120
Are you going or not? What do you say?

270
00:12:50,280 --> 00:12:52,760
Is proving yourself that important to you?

271
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:55,200
Of course it's important.

272
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:57,130
Our workload is so heavy right now.

273
00:12:57,240 --> 00:12:59,160
We shouldn't distract ourselves with other things.

274
00:12:59,160 --> 00:13:01,640
I already said we'd participate in our spare time.

275
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:04,200
Besides, don't you want to do more?

276
00:13:05,280 --> 00:13:06,400
Is that necessary?

277
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,800
Forget it. Suit yourself.

278
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:12,040
I have a way.

279
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:18,360
But for this competition,

280
00:13:18,360 --> 00:13:20,480
we need at least six people.

281
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:21,920
It's fine.

282
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:24,320
I know a bigger master

283
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:26,440
who isn't as arrogant as him.

284
00:13:32,040 --> 00:13:32,840
Later,

285
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:34,770
I'll introduce two friends to you.

286
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:42,080
Come on, cheers!

