380
00:17:42,920 --> 00:17:44,120
We failed, didn't we?

381
00:17:44,920 --> 00:17:46,600
Luring him into the trap

382
00:17:47,080 --> 00:17:48,960
involves two small steps.

383
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:51,040
Lure him,

384
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:52,960
into the trap.

385
00:17:54,480 --> 00:17:56,760
A willing victim lets himself be caught.

386
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:59,760
That's the only way to deal with his kind.

387
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:02,660
Let's discuss tonight

388
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:03,680
the next step.

389
00:18:04,400 --> 00:18:05,120
The trap.

390
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:07,640
Bro, give it a kick.

391
00:18:09,760 --> 00:18:10,440
Let's go.

392
00:18:13,040 --> 00:18:16,600
The Earth is the cradle of humanity,

393
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:21,360
but mankind cannot stay in the cradle forever.

394
00:18:22,360 --> 00:18:24,000
If people are no longer satisfied

395
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,600
with being citizens of the solar system,

396
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:27,860
how should they migrate to the Milky Way?

397
00:18:28,280 --> 00:18:29,920
The topic of this competition is

398
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:32,360
the design of migration orbits in the Milky Way.

399
00:18:32,360 --> 00:18:34,680
Galactic migration.

400
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:39,000
With the immigrable Milky Way as the background,

401
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:44,120
over a period of 90 million years,

402
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:48,770
three types of interstellar spaceships will be used

403
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:53,600
to spread humans throughout the Milky Way.

404
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:58,040
Taking 100,000 stars in the Milky Way

405
00:18:58,040 --> 00:19:00,200
as immigrable targets,

406
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:02,280
they are distributed

407
00:19:02,280 --> 00:19:05,720
within a range of about 210,000 light-years in diameter.

408
00:19:06,520 --> 00:19:08,240
The migration pod uses speed maneuvers

409
00:19:08,240 --> 00:19:09,600
to reach the star.

410
00:19:10,040 --> 00:19:12,300
The star is then immediately colonized.

411
00:19:12,320 --> 00:19:13,120
Each fast ship

412
00:19:13,120 --> 00:19:15,240
can only rendezvous with one star.

413
00:19:15,560 --> 00:19:16,820
The rendezvoused star

414
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:18,640
is immediately colonized.

415
00:19:18,640 --> 00:19:19,760
That means

416
00:19:20,040 --> 00:19:22,040
we have to compare migration plans.

417
00:19:24,280 --> 00:19:26,360
What a sci-fi topic!

418
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:27,240
Yeah.

419
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:29,040
This is the first time

420
00:19:29,040 --> 00:19:31,440
