443
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:26,680
It's fine. Don't worry.

444
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:27,240
We...

445
00:20:27,240 --> 00:20:29,300
Let's take our time and figure it out.

446
00:20:32,080 --> 00:20:32,920
No, Wei.

447
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:34,560
I really think it's a bit hard.

448
00:20:34,560 --> 00:20:35,760
It's fine, it's fine.

449
00:20:36,280 --> 00:20:38,340
I'll copy down their formulas first.

450
00:20:54,240 --> 00:20:55,120
In a two-body model,

451
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:57,200
gravity is inversely proportional to the square of the radius.

452
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:58,320
But the problem given is that

453
00:20:58,320 --> 00:20:59,360
at the very center of the Milky Way,

454
00:20:59,360 --> 00:21:00,120
gravity and radius

455
00:21:00,120 --> 00:21:01,840
have an inverse relationship of a higher-degree polynomial.

456
00:21:01,840 --> 00:21:02,560
So,

457
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:04,720
when calculating an interstellar transfer orbit,

458
00:21:04,720 --> 00:21:05,600
you can't simply apply

459
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:08,120
the common formulas under a two-body gravity environment

460
00:21:08,120 --> 00:21:08,960
and methods.

461
00:21:15,560 --> 00:21:16,890
It's actually not hard.

462
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:20,080
It mainly lies in the design of the migration tree.

463
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:21,080
Right.

464
00:21:21,560 --> 00:21:22,000
Right.

465
00:21:22,360 --> 00:21:23,720
That's exactly what I mean.

466
00:21:23,720 --> 00:21:24,650
Not hard, right?

467
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:31,890
I'll hang up now.

468
00:21:31,920 --> 00:21:32,720
I'm a bit hungry.

469
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:34,580
I'll grab a bite and call you back.

470
00:21:40,040 --> 00:21:41,600
The questions this year weren't that hard.

471
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:42,730
Good luck to you all.

472
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:44,360
Keep bragging.

473
00:21:44,360 --> 00:21:45,220
Keep bragging.

474
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:47,480
Qi, Qi, Qi.

475
00:21:47,840 --> 00:21:48,760
Qi, Qi, Qi.

476
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:50,000
Come, come, come.

477
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:52,250
Sit down.

478
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:55,040
Qi,

479
00:21:55,320 --> 00:21:56,600
